symptoms: Eschar (dark, scab-like region at the site of the chigger bite)
Pain, numbness, weakness or coldness in legs or arms
Pain in the neck, jaw, throat, upper abdomen or back
Persistent cough (lasting more than three weeks)
Rapid loss of body fluids leading to dehydration and shock
Yellowing of the skin and eyes (jaundice)
Skin lesions that may be faded/discolored
Numbness on affected areas of the skin
Muscle weakness or paralysis (especially in the hands and feet)
Eye problems that may lead to blindness
Enlargement of the spleen and liver
